.TH "nft_parse_u32_check" 9 "nft_parse_u32_check" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
nft_parse_u32_check \- fetch u32 attribute and check for maximum value
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" nft_parse_u32_check
.BI "(const struct nlattr *attr "  ","
.BI "int max "  ","
.BI "u32 *dest "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "attr" 12
netlink attribute to fetch value from
.IP "max" 12
maximum value to be stored in dest
.IP "dest" 12
pointer to the variable

Parse, check and store a given u32 netlink attribute into variable.
This function returns -ERANGE if the value goes over maximum value.
Otherwise a 0 is returned and the attribute value is stored in the
destination variable.
